%main.work
    %section.summary
        %p.large The goal of this discovery project was to research the sentiment and needs of the current IBM alumni population and generate possible initiatives, products and/or services that would help IBM better connect with current and future alumni and build a lasting community.
        %p.large This project was completed at Ignite in partnership with our sister company, Lee Hecht Harrison.

    %section 
        %h2.s4 Gauging alumni sentiment
        %p We analyzed IBM’s Glassdoor and LinkedIn statistics and interactions, reviewed and classified results from Lee Hecht Harrison’s alumni sentiment survey, and conducted many in-depth alumni interviews via video chat. From this research we identified three personas and their general needs, desires, and feelings towards IBM.
        %figure.img-left
            %img.lazy{:data => {:srcset => "../images/ibm-2a-500.jpg 500w, ../images/ibm-2a-1000.jpg 1000w, ../images/ibm-2a-2000.jpg 2000w", :sizes => "(max-width: 991px) 100vw, (max-width: 1439) 60vw, 850px", :src => "../images/ibm-2a-1000.jpg"}, :alt => "Several sticky notes grouped by categories for a millenial persona."}
            %figcaption.small
                %strong Post-its for days. 
                Each group mapped a different persona journey from separation from the company to finding a new opportunity. We then identified pain points and opportunities to connect and provide value.

    %section 
        %h2.s4 Diverge, converge, repeat
        %p I facilitated two ideation sessions during the 12-week project. The first session was conducted with several members of the Ignite team. The second ideation was held in New York City with members of IBM, Lee Hecht Harrison, and the Ignite project team. From these design-thinking workshops, we generated 127 ideas that centered around the themes of communication, connection, and knowledge sharing.
        %figure.img-right
            %figcaption.small
                %strong Frustration and laughter.
                One of the biggest challenges of the project was getting IBM and Lee Hecht Harrison leadership to think in new ways about alumni and their challenges. I used several empathy-building, design-thinking techniques to get them to open up.
            %img.lazy{:data => {:srcset => "../images/ibm-3a-500.jpg 500w, ../images/ibm-3a-1000.jpg 1000w, ../images/ibm-3a-2000.jpg 2000w", :sizes => "(max-width: 991px) 100vw, (max-width: 1439) 60vw, 850px", :src => "../images/ibm-3a-1000.jpg"}, :alt => "A group of IBM and Lee Hecht Harrison employees laugh as they take a break from the ideation session."}

    %section 
        %h2.s4 Testing digital solutions
        %p Based on our research and ideation process, we made recommendations for ways in which IBM and Lee Hecht Harrison could use their strengths to implement and test various initiatives. At Ignite, we chose to explore the possibility of a digital solution that would focus on communication, connection, and/or knowledge sharing.
        %p With the help of several Igniters, we put the ideas through an initial vetting process, fleshing out many of the ideas with sketches and listing assumptions and possible tests. After deciding on the final four ideas, we used 2-3 week sprints to prototype and test them.
        %figure.img-left
            %img.lazy{:data => {:srcset => "../images/ibm-4a-500.jpg 500w, ../images/ibm-4a-1000.jpg 1000w, ../images/ibm-4a-2000.jpg 2000w", :sizes => "(max-width: 991px) 100vw, (max-width: 1439) 60vw, 850px", :src => "../images/ibm-4a-1000.jpg"}, :alt => "2 sheets of paper with sketches on them."}
            %figcaption.small
                %strong Mind maps and crazy eights.
                Just two of the many exercises used for ideation. 

    %section 
        %h2.s4 Idea 1: an interactive timeline
        %p In the spirit of the popular StoryCorps project — “an American non-profit organization whose mission is to record, preserve, and share the stories of Americans” — we explored the possibility of developing a tool that would facilitate sharing the history of IBM through its people. This multimedia platform would provide a collective representation of IBM made up of imagery and information about previous projects and the people who worked on them.
        %figure.img-right
            %figcaption.small
                %strong The visual timeline would show stories in a beautiful, interactive matrix.
                For each project, alumni could add stories and tag fellow collaborators.
            %img.lazy{:data => {:srcset => "../images/ibm-5a-500.jpg 500w, ../images/ibm-5a-1000.jpg 1000w, ../images/ibm-5a-2000.jpg 2000w", :sizes => "(max-width: 991px) 100vw, (max-width: 1439) 60vw, 850px", :src => "../images/ibm-5a-1000.jpg"}, :alt => "A comp of a project page in the interactive timeline."}
